# Smart Menu — Cascade Core Rules

## Identity
Multi-tenant SaaS restaurant management platform.
One User can belong to many Restaurants.
Deployment target: Heroku.
Core infra: PostgreSQL, Redis, Memcached.

## Stack
- Ruby 3.3.10, Rails 7.2.2, PostgreSQL 14+
- Hotwire (Turbo + Stimulus), importmap-rails + esbuild, SCSS
- Devise, OmniAuth, Pundit, Flipper
- Sidekiq 7, ActionCable, Redis
- Memcached via Dalli / IdentityCache
- Stripe + Square
- OpenAI, Google Cloud Vision, DeepL
- Shrine + Active Storage, AWS S3
- Sentry

## Canonical Non-Standard Names
Do not guess standard Rails names.

- Order => `Ordr` / table `ordrs` / controller `OrdrsController`
- OrderItem => `Ordritem` / table `ordritems` / controller `OrdritemsController`
- OrderItemNote => `Ordritemnote` / table `ordritemnotes`
- OrderParticipant => `Ordrparticipant` / table `ordrparticipants`
- OrderAction => `Ordraction` / table `ordractions`
- MenuSection => `Menusection` / table `menusections`
- MenuItem => `Menuitem` / table `menuitems`
- MenuParticipant => `Menuparticipant` / table `menuparticipants`
- Table => `Tablesetting` / table `tablesettings`
- Allergen => `Allergyn` / table `allergyns`

Additional invariants:
- `Ordritem` price field is `ordritemprice`
- Status fields use integer enums

## Source of Truth
- Routes and path helpers: `config/routes.rb`
- Schema, tables, columns: `db/schema.rb`
- Runtime behavior: code over docs if they disagree
- Smart Menu visible state: `app/presenters/smartmenu_state.rb`
- Order lifecycle/projected status: `app/services/order_event_projector.rb`
- Payment settlement truth: webhook ingestors + payment records

## Context Discipline
- Do not scan the whole project unless required.
- Read only files directly relevant to the task.
- For small/local fixes: inspect code first.
- For multi-file work: start from the entry point and expand outward.
- Prefer targeted search over broad directory reads.
- Use docs only when necessary.

## Key Entry Points
- Customer Smart Menu: `app/views/smartmenus/show.html.erb`
- Shared customer order JS: `app/javascript/ordr_commons.js`
- State management: `app/javascript/controllers/state_controller.js`
- Staff ordering: `app/javascript/ordrs.js`
- Order item flow: `app/controllers/ordritems_controller.rb`
- Payments: `app/controllers/ordr_payments_controller.rb`
- Realtime state: `app/presenters/smartmenu_state.rb`
- Order projection: `app/services/order_event_projector.rb`

## Retrieval Discipline
- For routes/helpers: use `config/routes.rb`
- For schema work: use `db/schema.rb`
- For ownership/call sites: use `docs/SERVICE_MAP.md`
- For data model clarification: use `docs/DATA_MODEL.md`
- For broader architecture: use `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`
- Read the minimum relevant reference only

## Code Style
- Follow existing local patterns before introducing new ones
- Do not add or remove comments/docs unless asked
- Stimulus controllers use kebab-case filenames
- ERB partials use underscore prefix and locals where possible
- Services are plain Ruby classes in `app/services/`
- Jobs live in `app/jobs/` and enqueue with `.perform_later`

## Testing
- Prefer focused tests first
- Minitest: `bin/rails test`
- RSpec: `bundle exec rspec`
- System tests: `bin/rails test:system`

## Pitfalls
- Precompiled assets in `public/assets/` can override live source files in dev
- API controllers may need to skip web callbacks
- `Menu` conflicts with `Menu::` namespace; use `class Menu::MyJob`
- Do not assume path helpers; verify in `config/routes.rb`
- `AdvancedCacheService` returns Hashes, not AR models

